THE RUSTING PHYLACTERY
GM Reference Block - Alfonso's Iron Soul
"The weakest possible lich. Not immortal. Undying."

I. THE CORE PHILOSOPHY: THE TETHERED SOUL

During the camp between Mzinchaleft and Riften, Alfonso poured his soul into his
family's iron dagger. The iron reshaped itself into a corroded rapier as the enchantment
remade the weapon. His body became an empty vessel - and the rapier became the only
thing in the world that can kill him.

He is a Lich of Peryite, an oxymoron made empty. A traditional lich's phylactery is
hidden, hoarded, protected. Alfonso's is in his hand, in every fight, swung at enemies -
and it is slowly, inevitably rusting. He cannot be wounded. He can only corrode. The
threat is never the blow he takes; it is the power he spends.

Peryite does not mock the rust. Alfonso feels his own god radiating approval at the
mechanical perfection of entropy operating on schedule. The Taskmaster finds the
degradation beautiful. The rust is natural. The rust is ordered. The rust is exactly how
things should work. His own god approves of his death, and that is driving him insane.

II. THE EMPTY VESSEL (PASSIVE)

Alfonso's physical body has NO hit points and cannot be reduced to them.
- He takes NO damage from any conventional source - blades, arrows, claws, falls, fire,
  spells. Attacks pass through his shifting, rotting mass without effect.
- Immune to poison, disease, bleed, critical hits, and instant-death effects targeting
  the body.
- He cannot be knocked unconscious, stunned by pain, or killed by HP loss. There is no
  HP to lose.
- He still occupies space, can be grappled/moved/restrained, and can be affected by
  conditions that target the soul or enchantment directly (see Section VI).

There is exactly ONE way to harm Alfonso: advance the Rust. He does this to himself
every time he channels real power. An enemy can only do it if they learn the secret.

III. THE RUST - TWO TIERS

Rust is tracked in two layers. Surface Rust is the cost of doing business. Deep Rust is
the clock counting down to his end.

A. SURFACE RUST (Recoverable) - Pool of 10
The pitting and tarnish of ordinary use. Accrues fast, scrubs off with feeding and rest.
This is his renewable resource - the price of casting without bleeding a real wound.

GAINS Surface Rust from:
- The Transmutation of Life: when he pays a spell's FP cost in vitality instead of FP,
  he gains Surface Rust equal to that FP cost. (Free action, once per turn, before
  casting. Also taught to Nora, who pays in Irreducible Damage instead - she has a body.)
- Channeling high-tier magic through the rapier under strain: +1 Surface (GM call).
- Corrosive environments (acid, brine, certain Dwemer steam, Peryite shrines): +1 Surface
  per significant exposure.

RECOVERS Surface Rust by:
- Feeding: a full feed (consuming flesh) scrubs 2 Surface Rust as the husk stabilizes.
- Long Rest: a Long Rest taken AFTER feeding clears all remaining Surface Rust. A Long
  Rest without feeding clears half (round down).

THE OVERFLOW (the bridge to permanent doom):
If Surface Rust would exceed 10, it does not cap - the excess corrodes the core of the
blade. Each point of overflow converts into +1 Deep Rust segment, permanently. Burning
hot in a single day is how the blade ages years in an afternoon.

B. DEEP RUST (Permanent) - The Doom Clock, 10 Segments
The structural corrosion of the iron itself. This NEVER recovers by any ordinary means.
It is the "months not years" that Hjolmar diagnosed. It is the rust that has begun
migrating into Alfonso's flesh. When it fills, the blade shatters and Alfonso is
destroyed forever.

GAINS Deep Rust (1 segment each, unless noted) from:
- Major Channeling: any single act of supreme violence through the rapier - the
  triple-charge beam, corridor-clearing blasts, the harmony-blast finishers, any single
  ability costing 8+ FP in one action. Each one is +1 Deep segment. (The Krosulhah
  triple-beam already cost a segment; that is why his skin began to spot.)
- Surface Overflow: +1 per overflow point, as above.
- The Crown's "Digested Shout": when the Jagged Crown digests a held Shout, the effect
  that would deal "half max HP as irreducible damage" has no HP to land on - it converts
  to +1 Deep Rust instead.
- An Informed Sunder: a successful Sunder/corrode strike against the blade by an enemy
  who KNOWS it is his phylactery (see Section IV) = +1 Deep segment.
- Catastrophic story beats: GM discretion (a dragon's full breath caught on the blade, a
  Daedric backlash, a botched ritual).

DEEP RUST ONLY GOES DOWN ONE WAY: the Path of Ascension gamble (Section VII).

IV. THE EXPOSED SECRET (THE ONLY COMBAT THREAT)

The rapier is always in plain sight. He fights with it. It is not hidden, warded, or
disguised. The weak point is fully exposed - and almost no one knows to aim for it.

- An enemy must KNOW the rapier is Alfonso's phylactery to threaten it. Until they know,
  every attack they make against him does nothing, and they will likely waste a fight
  flailing at an unkillable opponent.
- Once an enemy knows, they can Sunder or corrode the blade directly. A successful strike
  against the blade adds +1 Deep Rust. This is the ONLY way an outside force can advance
  his doom clock - and it requires both the knowledge and getting past Alfonso to reach
  the iron.

WHO KNOWS / COULD LEARN:
- Hjolmar KNOWS. He studied Alfonso for days in the forge and "heard his dissonance." He
  is the single most dangerous entity to the blade and will exploit it the instant it
  serves him.
- Davinia's Wizard Sight perceives that his body has no aura - she has SEEN the wrongness
  but not named it. Saijah's predator senses flagged the transformation. Neither has
  confronted him.
- Antoine of Forelhost, a clinical bioweapon engineer, could deduce it from residue and
  rivalry if he gets close enough.
- The party protecting the secret of the blade becomes a campaign-long liability. The
  moment it leaks, Alfonso has a kill-switch walking around in the world.

V. THE DEGRADATION STAGES (Deep Rust migrating into the flesh)

"Not death. Degradation. The slow process of becoming the thing he's tethered to: a
corroding piece of metal in the shape of a man." Each stage is permanent. Penalties
apply to the body; they never threaten HP (he has none) - they erode what he can DO.

SEG 1-2  STAGE 0 - PITTED IRON
  Rust confined to the blade. The rapier looks ancient, scaled with corrosion. No effect
  on Alfonso. Cosmetic dread only.

SEG 3-4  STAGE 1 - THE FIRST BLOOM   <-- CURRENT NARRATIVE POSITION
  Rust spots bloom on Alfonso's skin - knuckles, jaw, the backs of the hands. Faint
  metallic smell under the grave-dirt. No mechanical penalty yet. The party can SEE it
  now if they look. (He is here following Krosulhah.)

SEG 5-6  STAGE 2 - STIFFENING
  Joints stiffen; iron corruption visible at the seams of him. Movement reduced; -1 to
  his Agility Target Number. Fine manipulation (alchemy, delicate spellwork) takes longer.

SEG 7-8  STAGE 3 - THE TARNISHED HUSK
  Widespread corrosion. Skin hardens toward metal; he flakes when he moves. -2 to Agility
  TN (replaces Stage 2) and -1 to Might TN. He now reads visibly as a "thing," not a man -
  social penalties with anyone who doesn't already know what he is.

SEG 9    STAGE 4 - THE IRON SHROUD
  Near-total petrification. Barely mobile. -2 to Agility and Might TN, -1 to Magic TN; he
  can take only one action per turn that involves movement OR a physical gesture, not
  both. He is, functionally, a corroding statue that still speaks and hungers.

SEG 10   STAGE 5 - SHATTER (DEATH)
  The blade cracks through. See Section VI.

VI. THE TWO FAILURE POINTS

SHATTER (Deep Rust hits 10, or an informed enemy destroys the blade):
- Permanent, irreversible death. The soul housed in the iron is destroyed with it.
- No resurrection, no Soul Cairn, no re-housing. This is the absolute end of Alfonso.
- When it happens, the husk collapses into inert rotting matter the instant the iron
  fails - the body has nothing left to animate it.

BODY DESTROYED while the blade survives:
- He is undying as long as the iron holds. If the husk is dismembered, burned, dissolved,
  or otherwise "destroyed," it is not death - it is inconvenience.
- The body reknits near the rapier over time (GM: minutes for minor damage, up to a full
  rest for total destruction). The soul simply grows a new vessel around its anchor.
- This is the lich's true horror: you cannot kill him by killing him. You have to find,
  reach, and break the sword.

VII. THE ONLY CURE (AND IT IS A GAMBLE)

Deep Rust cannot be healed by rest, feeding, magic, or divine intervention. The single
possibility of reversing it is the Path of Ascension (Alfonso arc, Option A): channeling
the heart of a Dragon Priest (Rahgot) and the heart of a Vampire Lord (Valerius) THROUGH
the rapier - piercing the heart and drinking its power the way a vampire drinks blood,
because the soul lives in the blade now, not the mouth.

Each heart consumed this way resolves as a gamble (GM sets the check):
- On success: the raw essence scours and re-tempers the iron - remove a meaningful chunk
  of Deep Rust (GM: 2-3 segments per heart).
- On failure: the power is too much for corroded iron to contain - it ACCELERATES the
  decay catastrophically (add segments, or jump him a full Stage).

The Apotheosis either saves him or finishes him. He will not know which until he commits.
The Path of Ascension problem (whether his endgame form is even still reachable as a
lich) must be resolved before the Valerius hunt - he needs to know if there's a finish
line before he bleeds the blade chasing it.

VIII. INTERACTIONS

- The Crown's Curse of Satedness and the phylactery's Diminished Hunger STACK and
  reinforce. Feeding now does two jobs and satisfies neither craving: it scrubs Surface
  Rust (mechanical) but delivers no fullness (Crown) and no empowerment high (phylactery).
  Eating is maintenance on a machine he hates being.
- Symbiotic Minion Control is unaffected by lichdom - he still runs up to two Plague
  Ghouls. (Control is absolute while Satiated; if forced to Hungry stage he rolls Guile
  each round or they turn.) Note he is permanently Hungry psychologically via the Crown,
  but can still reach mechanical Satiated by feeding.
- Plague touch, plague ghouls, and disease alchemy all still function - his body is a
  walking biohazard with or without a soul in it.
- Nora learned the Transmutation of Life from him. She pays in Irreducible Damage (she
  has HP); he pays in Surface Rust. Watching her bleed for power while he rusts for it is
  the whole mentorship in one image.

IX. CURRENT STATE (as of Riften / present reality)

- Deep Rust: Stage 1 (segments 3-4) - skin spots have appeared. The triple-charge beam
  against Krosulhah pushed him here. He is "one hit point of rust away" from Stiffening.
- Surface Rust: GM-tracked; reset each rest cycle.
- The party views him as "Alfonso but weirder." They do not understand the full stakes.
  Davinia and Saijah have sensed wrongness without naming it.
- Antoine / the Forelhost Strain rivalry is upcoming in Riften; Antoine is a candidate to
  one day deduce the blade.

X. GM NOTES & PACING

- The doom clock is PLAYER-PACED, not session-paced (unlike the Dragon Cult clock). The
  more spectacular Alfonso's power, the faster he dies. Let every triple-beam land with
  the weight of "that was a piece of your life." Do not advance Deep Rust silently for
  ordinary play - reserve it for supreme violence, overflow, the digested-Shout, informed
  sunders, and story catastrophe.
- Alfonso's PLAYER should track and feel the clock. The rest of the PARTY should learn
  the stakes gradually through the visible Stages, not a number. Play the skin-spots, the
  stiffening, the flaking - let them figure out their friend is dying by inches.
- Peryite's approval is a recurring RP beat, not a mechanic. Every time the rust advances,
  let Alfonso feel that warm, horrible divine nod. His god is pleased. That is the worst
  part.
- The secret of the blade is a social time-bomb. Track who knows. Hjolmar already does -
  a future Hjolmar-Kyboh encounter where he ignores the whole party and goes straight for
  Alfonso's sword is a devastating reveal that he KNOWS.
- The cure is a trap dressed as hope. The Path of Ascension gamble should feel like the
  only door out and like russian roulette. Make him weigh it.

XI. QUICK REFERENCE

Surface Rust ...... pool 0-10, recoverable. Transmutation = +FP cost. Feed = -2.
                    Rest after feed = clear all. Overflow past 10 = +1 Deep each.
Deep Rust ......... clock 0-10, permanent. Major channel (8+ FP / supreme act) = +1.
                    Overflow = +1 each. Digested Shout = +1. Informed sunder = +1.
                    Only the heart-gamble removes it.
Stages ............ 0 Pitted (blade only) | 1 First Bloom (skin spots, no penalty)
                    2 Stiffening (-1 Agi) | 3 Tarnished Husk (-2 Agi, -1 Might)
                    4 Iron Shroud (-2 Agi/Might, -1 Magic, one physical action)
                    5 SHATTER = permanent death
Combat damage ..... NONE. Body cannot be hurt. Rust is the only threat.
The kill-switch ... break the blade. Requires knowing it is the phylactery.
Body destroyed .... reknits near the intact blade. Truly undying until the iron breaks.
